Cook Time: 8 mins*
*Depends on size of cookie

Ingredients:
- 1/2 cup butter
- 1/2 cup brown sugar
- 1/4 cup granulated sugar
- 1 large egg
- 2 tsp vanilla extract
- 1 cup + 1 tbsp all purpose flour
- 2 tbsp corn starch
- 1/2 tsp baking soda
- 1/2 tsp salt
- 3/4 cup chocolate chips (semi-sweet)
- 1 cup crushed pretzels
- Sea salt for topping

Instructions
- Preheat oven to 350F, line baking sheet with parchment paper, set aside.

- In a mixer bowl, cream the butter and both sugars together until smooth and lighter in color.
- Add in the vanilla and the egg, mixing again until all is well incorporated

- Add in the dry ingredients over the wet mixture, in order of:
  - Flour
  - Corn starch
  - Baking soda
  - Salt
- Stir just until flour disappears

- Add crushed pretzels and chocolate chips, stirring to evenly distribute
- Use a spoon to place on baking sheet. Cook for 8 minutes or thereabout.
